revision.text: ==English== ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun|Yarboroughs}} # {{surname|en}}. ====Statistics==== * According to the 2010 United States Census, ''Yarborough'' is the 5119<sup>th</sup> most common surname in the United States, belonging to 6839 individuals. ''Yarborough'' is most common among White (66.08%) and Black/African American (29.4%) individuals. ===Noun=== {{en-noun}} # {{lb|en|bridge}} A [[hand]] that contains no [[honor]]s.
